Introduction {#Sec1}
============

The impact of physical activity pattern on health outcomes is an ongoing debate and has recently received considerable research attention^[@CR1]--[@CR6]^. It has been hypothesized, that long-term monitoring and pattern correction with respect to physical activity session frequency and distribution over time may facilitate rehabilitation and lead to a reduced number of deaths, caused by cardiovascular diseases^[@CR7],[@CR8]^.
